CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 14, 1959, p. A3, reads: "Part of the Crowd - Above is part of the crowd which witnessed the cornerstone laying at Loendi Club Sunday afternoon. The cornerstone itself was laid by a special team, as Masons from the western end of the state turned out en masse, together with members and friends of the organization."
TitMainTitle: Masonic procession passing through crowd, some with bowed heads and hats in hand, and photographers squatting on ground, for cornerstone laying of Loendi Club on Ledlie Street
